Package: cfrnow
Title: Real-Time Case Fatality Ratio via a Mixture-Cure Survival Model
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Sebastian", "Funk", , "sebastian.funk@lshtm.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Estimates a real-time case fatality ratio (CFR) from line-list data
    using a Bayesian mixture-cure survival model. Each case is fatal with
    probability equal to the CFR and, when fatal, dies at an interval-censored
    onset-to-death delay; cases still alive at the observation cut-off are
    right-censored, which corrects the downward bias of the naive deaths /
    cases ratio in real time. The onset-to-death delay is co-estimated using
    the primarycensored analytical censored-distribution machinery.
